begin_memory_text: We talked a little bit about work and hobbies we've picked up during the pandemic. He works as a ship captain and he's been trying to learn piano. He also did a lot of cooking and baking with a firend during the pandemic. He talked about taking turns cooking with a firend and having zoom meals. I talked a bit about how teaching online is going and what I'm teaching.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about traveling. He has been all over the world both for fun and for work when he worked on a research ship. He menitoned wanting to go to Morrocco and Iceland and Thailand were two trips that he had planned on doing but his trps got cancelled. I talked about some of the places I've been to and where I would want to go if I could.
end_memory_text: We continued talking about traveling. We talked about Japan a bit and how it's harder to get by not knowing the language there. We also mentioned how there are so many countries that it's common for people to just know english. rest_of_day_open: I have a lot of work to get done, so I will be spending most of the week working on writing ans creating lessons for my students. In the venings I will spend time getting personal chores done and finding time to relax and do things that I enjoy doing. I probably won't have as much free time this week as I usually do.
critical_positive: It overall went very well. We had a common interest of traveling and have both travelled quite a bit so we had a lot to talk about and it seemed pretty easy for both of us to come up with things to say. We also seemed to generally agree on our overall view of traveling so there weren't moments of disagreement or any negative emotions.
critical_negative: The beginning was a little ibt hard to get going. It wasn't bad, it just took us a bit of time to find a topic we were both able to talk a lot about, so we went around to a couple of different topics. There were times where it seemed like he either had no idea what to say, or he just wasn't interested at all in the conversation and was just watching the time, so I felt pressured to come up with something to keep the conversation going. I usually got this feeling when the conversation lulled and he would glance down but not say anything else or make any facial expression.

begin_memory_text: We talked about basic information about ourselves. Our names and what we did for work and where we lived. We talked about what we do for fun also.
middle_memory_text: We talked about what we did during the pandemic. Different hobbies we have and things we started during the pandemic. We talked about cooking and dinner parties and what some of our friends did during the pandemic.
end_memory_text: We mostly talked about traveling. Places we'd like to go, places we've already been. Where we would go if we could travel again. We talked about some of our favorite trips and the coolest places we've been.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will go well. I have a fair amount of stuff to accomplish but I think I will be able to get it all done. My schedule is pretty wide open at this point so I think I'll be able to get it all done. I have some things planned with friends which will be fun.
critical_positive: Everything worked well. We were able to find things to talk about and had some stuff in common. She was good at asking questions if there was a lull in the conversation which was nice. She had some interesting things going on in her life which made it easy for me to find things to ask her about too.
critical_negative: It can be hard to find things to talk about with a complete stranger so we started with some basic questions about what we did for work and details like that. It wasnt particularly bad it's just kind of an average getting to know you sort of scenario. It takes a little bit of effort to get over that initial awkward beginning to get the conversation to flow.
